# Building This App

Android app (Kotlin + Jetpack Compose), built with Gradle. minSdk 24, targetSdk 36.

## JDK

`java` is NOT on PATH. Use the JDK bundled with Android Studio by setting `JAVA_HOME`
for the command (PowerShell):

```powershell
$env:JAVA_HOME="C:\Program Files\Android\Android Studio\jbr"
```

## Common commands

Run from the repo root via the Gradle wrapper (`gradlew.bat` on Windows):

```powershell
# Fast type-check after Kotlin edits (preferred verification step)
.\gradlew.bat :app:compileDebugKotlin --console=plain

# Build a debug APK
.\gradlew.bat :app:assembleDebug --console=plain

# Install onto a connected device/glasses
.\gradlew.bat :app:installDebug --console=plain
```

After editing Kotlin, verify with `:app:compileDebugKotlin` — it's the quickest way to
catch errors without a full APK build.
